'''北极世界档案馆'''（{{lang-en|Arctic World Archive}}）是一个{{tsl|en|Data preservation||数据储存}}设施，位于[[挪威|挪威]][[斯瓦尔巴|斯瓦尔巴]]群岛，毗邻[[斯瓦尔巴全球种子库|斯瓦尔巴全球种子库]]。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Arctic World Archive - Piql|url=https://www.piql.com/arctic-world-archive/|accessdate=2018-04-16|publisher=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180418225459/https://www.piql.com/arctic-world-archive/|archivedate=2018-04-18|dead-url=no}}</ref>该设施由挪威[[私营公司|私营公司]]Piql与[[国有公司|国有]][[煤矿|煤矿]]公司{{le|Store Norske Spitsbergen Kulkompani}}（SNSK）运营，储有来自多个国家的历史与文化数据，以及跨国公司[[GitHub|GitHub]]的所有开源代码，存储介质预计可保存500年至1000年。设施于2017年3月27日开放。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Dommedagshvelv åpner på Svalbard|url=https://www.nrk.no/viten/xl/dommedagshvelv-apnes-pa-svalbard-1.13439547|accessdate=2018-04-16|author=NRK|date=2017-03-26|publisher=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180411210030/https://www.nrk.no/viten/xl/dommedagshvelv-apnes-pa-svalbard-1.13439547|archivedate=2018-04-11|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==历史==
Piql是挪威一家专门从事数字介质长期储存的数据存储公司。Piql与SNSK公司共同在一个废弃煤矿的[[矿井|矿井]]中建设了一个深埋的钢制拱顶。2017年3月27日档案馆开放日，巴西、墨西哥和挪威政府在该储藏库中存放了各种历史文件的副本。<ref name=vincent>{{cite web | last=Vincent | first=James | title=Keep your data safe from the apocalypse in an Arctic mineshaft | website=The Verge | date=4 April 2017 | url=https://www.theverge.com/2017/4/4/15159148/norway-data-vault-svalberd-mine-storage | access-date=13 August 2020 | archive-date=2019-12-22 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222152606/https://www.theverge.com/2017/4/4/15159148/norway-data-vault-svalberd-mine-storage | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nrk.no/viten/xl/dommedagshvelv-apnes-pa-svalbard-1.13439547|title=Dommedagshvelv åpner på Svalbard|last=NRK|publisher=|date=2017-03-26|access-date=2018-04-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180411210030/https://www.nrk.no/viten/xl/dommedagshvelv-apnes-pa-svalbard-1.13439547|archive-date=2018-04-11|lang=no|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.piql.com/arctic-world-archive/|title=Arctic World Archive - Piql|publisher=|access-date=2018-04-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180418225459/https://www.piql.com/arctic-world-archive/|archive-date=2018-04-18|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==介绍==
斯瓦尔巴群岛位于挪威大陆北部，距北极约{{convert|600|mi|order=flip}}<ref name=nbc/>，根据[[一战|一战]]后签署的一项条约，其已被42个国家/地区宣布非军事化<ref name=vincent/>，因此意味着该地不能用于军事目的，公司将该地点描述为“世界上最不受[[地缘政治|地缘政治]]影响的地方之一”<ref name=":0" /><ref name=lindner/>。档案馆位于斯瓦尔巴特群岛最大的岛屿[[斯匹次卑尔根岛|斯匹次卑尔根岛]]。<ref name=buried/>

该储藏库是一个大型钢制仓库<ref name=buried>{{cite web| title=Buried deep in the ice is the GitHub code vault| first=Nate| last=Byrne| website=ABC News| publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation| date=12 August 2020| url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-08-13/github-code-vault-in-artic-svalbard-safeguards-against-calamity/12517948| access-date=13 August 2020| archive-date=2020-11-15| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201115015832/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-08-13/github-code-vault-in-artic-svalbard-safeguards-against-calamity/12517948| dead-url=no}}</ref>，位于距山外300多米，距地面或[[永久冻土|永久冻土]]层约150米<ref name=":0"/>至300米<ref name=buried/><ref name=nbc/>的一座废弃煤矿内。<ref name=":0">{{cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2017/04/04/europe/doomsday-library-arctic-trnd/index.html|title=Arctic 'doomsday' vault seeks to protect world's most precious data|first=Paul|last=Lawlor|publisher=CNN|access-date=2018-04-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180418162243/https://edition.cnn.com/2017/04/04/europe/doomsday-library-arctic-trnd/index.html|archive-date=2018-04-18|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/norway-data-storage-vault|title=Norway's Doomsday vault will now store and protect the world's data|last=Kobie|first=Nicole|date=2017-04-03|work=Wired UK|access-date=2019-11-25|issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191108084227/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/norway-data-storage-vault|archive-date=2019-11-08|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://science.howstuffworks.com/environmental/earth/geology/arctic-world-archive-puts-data-ice-1000-years.htm|title=Arctic World Archive Puts Data on Ice for 1,000 Years|date=2017-04-04|website=HowStuffWorks|language=en|access-date=2019-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200402134145/https://science.howstuffworks.com/environmental/earth/geology/arctic-world-archive-puts-data-ice-1000-years.htm|archive-date=2020-04-02|dead-url=no}}</ref>设施由[[混凝土|混凝土]]墙和钢制大门保护。藏品在内部存放于安全的运输集装箱中。<ref>{{Cite web|date=2020-08-09|title=Diese Kohlemine soll das digitale Erbe der Menschheit schützen|url=https://1e9.community/t/diese-kohlemine-soll-das-digitale-erbe-der-menschheit-schuetzen/5102|access-date=2020-08-10|website=1E9|language=de|archive-date=2020-11-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201118201104/https://1e9.community/t/diese-kohlemine-soll-das-digitale-erbe-der-menschheit-schuetzen/5102|dead-url=no}}</ref>

因该岛的[[北极气候|北极气候]]和由此多年形成的永久冻土，即使该设施断电，位于永久冻土下方的储藏库内部的温度仍将保持在[[冰点|冰点]]以下，足以使储藏物品保存数十年以上<ref name=":0" />。储藏库的位置足够深，可避免受到[[核武器|核武器]]和[[电磁脉冲|电磁脉冲]]武器的损害。<ref name=":1" />

==储存和未来用途==
数据被离线储存于数字[[胶片|胶片]]，报道称寿命为至少500年，乃至长达1000年（另一说预计使用寿命750年，最佳存储条件下可达2000年<ref name=lindner/>）。<ref name=vincent/><ref name=nbc/>所用材料是按普通暗室摄影技术改进制成的电影胶片，薄膜是涂有[[卤化银|卤化银]]晶体的[[聚酯|聚酯]]<ref name=buried/>，并使用[[氧化铁|氧化铁]]涂层。<ref name=lindner/>

为防将来的人们不了解储存库中的内容，故设计了一种[[罗塞塔石碑|罗塞塔石碑]]形式的指南来帮助解释如何解码数据。所有指南在放大后都[[人类可读介质|可用肉眼阅读]]，且是以英语、阿拉伯语、西班牙语、中文和北印度语书写。<ref name=buried/>

==流程==
支付数据存储费用的客户可用数字或物理方式发送其数据。用户可以随时检索储藏库中的数据，但需要时间，因为数据并未连接[[互联网|互联网]]。如果需要数据，则必须手动检索相关胶卷<ref name=vincent/>，然后通过[[光纤|光纤]]连接上传到Piql于[[德拉门|德拉门]]的总部<ref name=nbc>{{cite web | title=Look inside the doomsday vault that may hold the world’s most important data | website=NBC News | date=7 June 2017 | url=https://www.nbcnews.com/mach/innovation/look-inside-doomsday-vault-may-hold-world-s-most-important-n769341 | access-date=13 August 2020 | archive-date=2018-04-17 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180417122345/https://www.nbcnews.com/mach/innovation/look-inside-doomsday-vault-may-hold-world-s-most-important-n769341 | dead-url=no }}</ref>，检索最快需要20-30分钟，但通常会更久。<ref name=vincent/>

==藏品==
档案馆存储了众多的历史与文化数据。<ref name=buried/>政府、研究人员、宗教机构、媒体公司和其他公司已将一些重要的记录放于储存库中。巴西和挪威已将其[[宪法|宪法]]和其他重要的历史文献存档。<ref name=nbc/>

藏品包括[[澳大利亚|澳大利亚]]的[[生物多样性|生物多样性]]信息，以及一些具有文化意义的澳大利亚作品。<ref name=buried/>

藏品还包括重要作品的数字化版本，如挪威国家博物馆的[[爱德华·蒙克|爱德华·蒙克]]作品《[[吶喊_(繪畫)|吶喊]]》的[[数字化|数字化]]版本，意大利文学大师[[但丁·阿利吉耶里|但丁]]的杰作的数字化版本，[[梵蒂岡宗座圖書館|梵蒂岡宗座圖書館]]的《[[神曲|神曲]]》等。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.groene.nl/artikel/rembrandt-in-de-permafrost|title=Alles van waarde ligt straks in een oude mijnschacht op Spitsbergen|publisher=|access-date=2018-04-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180418161546/https://www.groene.nl/artikel/rembrandt-in-de-permafrost|archive-date=2018-04-18|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2018年3月，德国电视科学节目伽利略（Galileo）存放了其首场演出，并为{{le|ProSieben}}制作了一部相关的纪录片。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prosieben.de/tv/galileo/videos/201875-der-datenbunker-spitzbergen-clip|title=Galileo - Der Datenbunker Spitzbergen|publisher=|date=2018-03-19|access-date=2018-04-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180418162055/https://www.prosieben.de/tv/galileo/videos/201875-der-datenbunker-spitzbergen-clip|archive-date=2018-04-18|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=galileo>{{cite web | title=German TV program on Piql watched by millions | website=Piql | date=19 April 2018 | url=https://www.piql.com/german-tv-program-on-piql-watched-by-millions/ | access-date=13 August 2020 | archive-date=2020-10-21 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201021055107/https://www.piql.com/german-tv-program-on-piql-watched-by-millions/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>

==GitHub存档计划==
2019年11月，GitHub（于2018年被微软收购<ref name=lindner>{{cite web | last=Linder | first=Courtney | title=Github Code - Storing Code for the Apocalypse | website=Popular Mechanics | date=15 November 2019 | url=https://www.popularmechanics.com/technology/security/a29811351/microsoft-secret-code-vault/ | access-date=13 August 2020 | archive-date=2019-11-19 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191119030845/https://www.popularmechanics.com/technology/security/a29811351/microsoft-secret-code-vault/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>）宣布，作为“GitHub存档计划”的一部分，会将其所有的公开开源代码存储到“北极世界档案馆”。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.engadget.com/2019/11/15/github-store-public-open-source-code-arctic-vault/|title=GitHub will store all of its public open source code in an Arctic vault|website=Engadget|language=en|access-date=2019-11-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191115221339/https://www.engadget.com/2019/11/15/github-store-public-open-source-code-arctic-vault/|archive-date=2019-11-15|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/features/2019-11-13/microsoft-apocalypse-proofs-open-source-code-in-an-arctic-cave|title=Open Source Code Will Survive the Apocalypse in an Arctic Cave|last=Vance|first=Ashley|date=November 13, 2019|work=[[Bloomberg_Businessweek|Bloomberg Businessweek]]|access-date=November 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191117230310/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/features/2019-11-13/microsoft-apocalypse-proofs-open-source-code-in-an-arctic-cave|archive-date=2019-11-17|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=buried/>

2020年7月，21 [[terabyte|TB]]的存档（生成于同年2月）被存入北极世界档案馆。<ref>{{Cite web|title=GitHub Has Stored Its Code in an Arctic Vault It Hopes Will Last 1,000 Years|url=https://gizmodo.com/github-has-stored-its-code-in-an-arctic-vault-it-hopes-1844420340|access-date=2020-07-18|website=Gizmodo|archive-date=2020-10-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201008022102/https://gizmodo.com/github-has-stored-its-code-in-an-arctic-vault-it-hopes-1844420340|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=GitHub, the world's largest open-source software site, just had mounds of data stored in the permafrost chamber of an old coal mine deep in an Arctic mountain for 1,000 years|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/technology/github-the-worlds-largest-open-source-software-site-just-had-mounds-of-data-stored-in-the-permafrost-chamber-of-an-old-coal-mine-deep-in-an-arctic-mountain-for-1000-years/ar-BB16U75c|access-date=2020-07-18|website=www.msn.com|archive-date=2020-10-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201009010534/https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/technology/github-the-worlds-largest-open-source-software-site-just-had-mounds-of-data-stored-in-the-permafrost-chamber-of-an-old-coal-mine-deep-in-an-arctic-mountain-for-1000-years/ar-BB16U75c|dead-url=no}}</ref>数据被存储在长达1公里的186个胶片卷轴上，代码运用[[QR码|QR码]]形式存储，这样能非常密集的储存数据（每个卷轴储存120 [[吉字节|GB]]<ref name=lindner/>）。第一卷包含[[Linux|Linux]]和[[Android|Android]]操作系统的代码，以及其他6000个主要的开源[[应用程序|应用程序]]的代码。<ref name=lindner/>

除一般指南外，其中包含的“技术树”还详细介绍了[[软件开发|软件开发]]、[[编程语言|编程语言]]和其他有关计算机编程的信息。<ref name=buried/>

